---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
import PullQuote from '../components/PullQuote.astro';

const quotes = [
  'She could carry the name. She would not carry the lie.',
  'Some stories protect a family. Some protect the people who harmed it.',
  'Every family has a story. Not every family tells the truth.',
];
---

<BaseLayout
  active="novel"
  title="The Family Narrative — A Novel by Monica Messer"
  description="The Family Narrative is Monica Messer's debut novel — a story of marriage, money, reputation, motherhood, and the moment a woman stops protecting a story that was never really hers."
>
  <!-- HERO / SHORT SYNOPSIS (Card 3) -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container split">
      <div class="split-media">
        <img src="/assets/book-cover.png" alt="The Family Narrative by Monica Messer" class="cover-img" />
      </div>
      <div class="split-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Debut Novel</p>
        <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4.4vw,3.2rem);">A novel about reputation, marriage, money, and the moment a woman stops protecting a story that was never really hers.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Frances Stanton knows how to keep a life looking intact. She understands schedules,
          appearances, family obligations, and the invisible work required to make powerful
          people feel protected. When Dick files for divorce, she thinks the marriage is the crisis.
        </p>
        <p>
          But as financial reality, family loyalty, and institutional reputation collide, Frances
          begins to understand that the story the Stanton family wants to tell no longer matches
          the truth she and her sons are living. Now she must decide whether safety is worth the
          silence it requires.
        </p>
        <div class="btn-group">
          <a href="/read/" class="btn btn-primary">Start Reading Now</a>
          <a href="/read/#listen" class="btn btn-outline">Listen</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BACK COVER COPY (Card 4) -->
  <section class="bg-sand">
    <div class="container narrow backcover">
      <p class="eyebrow center">From the back cover</p>
      <h2 class="center">How much of a family's truth can be hidden inside a beautiful life?</h2>
      <p class="drop">
        For decades, Frances Stanton has lived inside a family story everyone else admired.
        Her husband, Dick, is the heir to one of Northern California's most prominent university
        families. The Stanton name means success, philanthropy, loyalty, and legacy. Frances has
        built a life around preserving that image — for her husband, for their sons, and for the
        institution that bears his family's name.
      </p>
      <p>Then Dick files for divorce.</p>
      <p>
        At first, Frances believes the end of her marriage is the crisis she must survive. But as
        the carefully polished Stanton narrative begins to crack, she discovers that the story
        everyone wanted her to protect has been protecting something else. The house, the accounts,
        the reputation, the friendships, the public statements — everything that once made her feel
        secure begins to reveal another truth.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>The Family Narrative</em> is a novel about a woman learning to distinguish loyalty from
        complicity, protection from control, and survival from silence. It is a story of marriage,
        money, motherhood, female friendship, and the courage it takes to stop carrying a story that
        harms the people you love.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THEMES GRID — full (Card 5) -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head center">
        <p class="eyebrow">Inside The Family Narrative</p>
        <h2>Six threads running through the novel</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-cards">
        <div class="theme-card">
          <h3>Marriage &amp; reputation</h3>
          <p>What does a wife owe a marriage once the truth is no longer private?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-card">
          <h3>Money &amp; dependence</h3>
          <p>Financial reality becomes impossible to ignore when the life Frances trusted begins to collapse.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-card">
          <h3>Motherhood &amp; moral clarity</h3>
          <p>Frances's sons force her to see what adults have been willing to minimize.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-card">
          <h3>Female friendship</h3>
          <p>The women on the porch do not rescue Frances. They help her hear herself.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-card">
          <h3>Power &amp; institutions</h3>
          <p>The university, the donors, and the family all know how to protect themselves.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="theme-card">
          <h3>Truth &amp; reinvention</h3>
          <p>Starting over begins with saying what is real.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PULL QUOTE (Card 8) -->
  <PullQuote quotes={quotes} extraClass="bg-sand2" />

  <!-- READER PROMISE (Card 6) -->
  <section>
    <div class="container narrow center">
      <p class="eyebrow">For readers who…</p>
      <h2>Love emotionally honest fiction about women's lives after the performance stops.</h2>
      <p class="lede measure">
        Drawn to domestic literary fiction, complicated marriages, family systems, moral reckonings,
        women in midlife, mother-son relationships, financial awakening, and the kind of friendship
        that tells the truth even when it hurts.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BOOK CLUB (Card 7) -->
  <section class="bg-slate">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#C9A96B;">For Book Clubs</p>
      <h2>A story made for the conversations women are finally ready to have.</h2>
      <p>
        <em>The Family Narrative</em> opens questions women often carry privately:
      </p>
      <ul class="qlist" style="color:#EDE6DA;">
        <li style="border-color:#475561;">What did I agree to without realizing it?</li>
        <li style="border-color:#475561;">What did I know but not want to see?</li>
        <li style="border-color:#475561;">When does loyalty become self-erasure?</li>
        <li style="border-color:#475561;">How much financial reality did I understand in my own life?</li>
        <li style="border-color:#475561;">What do we owe our children when the truth threatens the life we built?</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="btn-group" style="margin-top:32px;">
        <a href="/downloads/the-family-narrative-book-club-guide.pdf" class="btn btn-light" download>Download the Discussion Guide</a>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:.85rem;color:#C7BCAB;margin-top:18px;">
        A printable PDF with 13 discussion themes and a closing question — free to download now.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PLACEHOLDER LINKS (preorder / retailers / press kit) -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head center">
        <p class="eyebrow">Coming Soon</p>
        <h2>Where to find the book</h2>
        <p class="measure" style="margin:0 auto;">Preorder and retailer links will appear here as the launch approaches. Join the newsletter to be the first to know.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="placeholder-row">
        <div class="ph-item">
          <span class="label">Preorder</span>
          <div class="note">Link coming soon</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ph-item">
          <span class="label">Amazon &amp; Goodreads</span>
          <div class="note">Listings coming soon</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ph-item">
          <span class="label">Press Kit</span>
          <div class="note">Available on request soon</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ph-item">
          <span class="label">Book Club Materials</span>
          <div class="note"><a href="/downloads/the-family-narrative-book-club-guide.pdf" download>Discussion guide — download now</a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Newsletter />
</BaseLayout>
